'''Carl-Heinz Greve''' (17 October 1920 <U+2013> 21 May 1998) was a highly decorated [[Major]] in the [[Luftwaffe]] during [[World War II]], and a recipient of the [[Knight's Cross of the Iron Cross]]. The Knight's Cross of the Iron Cross was awarded to recognise extreme battlefield bravery or successful military leadership.  Carl-Heinz Greve joined the Bundeswehr in 1956 and retired in 1981 as a Generalleutnant.

==Awards and decorations==
* [[Aviator badge]]
* [[Front Flying Clasp of the Luftwaffe]] in Gold with Pennant "200" 
* [[Ehrenpokal der Luftwaffe]] (18 March 1942)
* [[Iron Cross]] (1939)
** 2nd Class (18 September 1941)
** 1st Class (11 October 1941)
* [[German Cross]] in Gold (2 July 1942)
* [[Knight's Cross of the Iron Cross]] on 7 October 1942 as ''[[Leutnant]]'' and pilot in the 3./Kampfgruppe 606<ref>Fellgiebel 2000, p. 169.</ref>
* [[Order of Merit of the Federal Republic of Germany]]
** [[Merit Cross 1st Class]] (15 May 1973)
** [[Great Cross of Merit]] (30 November 1974)

